(61, 1, '2016-11-10 20:47:48', '2016-11-10 20:47:48', '[vc_row row_type="row" use_row_as_full_screen_section="no" type="full_width" angled_section="no" text_align="left" background_image_as_pattern="without_pattern" background_color="#ffffff" css_animation=""][vc_column][vc_gmaps link="#E-8_"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="row" use_row_as_full_screen_section="no" type="grid" angled_section="no" text_align="left" background_image_as_pattern="without_pattern" background_color="#ffffff" padding_top="50" padding_bottom="34" css_animation=""][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">East Austin Movers</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_separator type="small" position="left" up="7" down="13"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4>Sir is so East Austin, He Listens To Bands That Don\'t Even Exist Yet!</h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_separator type="transparent" up="24" down="0"][vc_column_text]Being a proud Austinite Sir Austin knows how to keep it weird and there are lots of weird snags that can hamper a move in or out of East Austin. One of the biggest considerations you need to worry about is potholes and bad road conditions in general. That\'s why ratcheting down many layers of a moving truck is imperative. On a mainly highway move you can usually expect level streets and minimal potholes so planning your East Austin move should account for these conditions. Another equally important consideration to take into account is uneven streets. An uneven street can shift a truck from side to side more than even potholes so make sure to take these two into account.[/vc_column_text][vc_separator type="transparent" up="15" down="0"][vc_column_text]Another equally important consideration is low lying trees. Many East Austin streets are notorious for having low lying trees. Low lying trees can puncture holes in the top of a moving truck running the risk of exposing your belongings to the elements. Not only that but not paying attention to low branches can cause a safety concern by introducing the possibility of having a branch fall on another car or even worse, a person. Although these are mainly internal concerns to our moving company, Sir Austin dots his I\'s and crosses his t\'s whenever moving in and out of East Austin.[/vc_column_text][vc_separator type="transparent" up="42" down="0"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="149" img_size="1000x600" qode_css_animation=""][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="row" use_row_as_full_screen_section="no" type="grid" angled_section="no" text_align="left" background_image_as_pattern="without_pattern" padding_top="87" padding_bottom="87" css_animation=""][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Get Social With Sir Austin</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_separator type="small" position="center" up="7" down="37"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;">Connect with Sir Austin on one of his social channels</h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_separator type="transparent" up="55" down="0"][qode_circles columns="five_columns" circle_line="with_line" line_color="#f1f1f1"][qode_circle type="icon_type" icon="fa-facebook" size="fa-4x" border_width="8" icon_color="#ffffff" background_color="#cfcfcf" border_color="#f1f1f1"][qode_circle type="icon_type" icon="fa-twitter" size="fa-4x" border_width="8" icon_color="#ffffff" background_color="#cfcfcf" border_color="#f1f1f1"][qode_circle type="icon_type" icon="fa-google-plus" size="fa-4x" border_width="8" icon_color="#ffffff" background_color="#cfcfcf" border_color="#f1f1f1"][qode_circle type="icon_type" icon="fa-linkedin" size="fa-4x" border_width="8" icon_color="#ffffff" background_color="#cfcfcf" border_color="#f1f1f1"][qode_circle type="icon_type" icon="fa-instagram" size="fa-4x" border_width="8" icon_color="#ffffff" background_color="#cfcfcf" border_color="#f1f1f1"][/qode_circles][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'East Austin Moving', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'east-austin-moving', '', '', '2016-11-13 1