(195, 1, '2016-11-11 06:14:24', '2016-11-11 06:14:24', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">Whenever you think about a <a href="http://siraustinmovers.com">moving company</a> you normally think about a few guys, packaging a truck up with your belongings and driving off. However it hasn’t always been such a cut and dry proposition. Migration, thus moving, has been something people have been doing since the dawn of time. Various tribes have banned together over the years to cross vast planes of land throughout the world. The technology of moving things from one point to another has evolved overtime with different technological achievements to arrive at the place it is today. It wasn’t until later did moving businesses appear to provide relocation as a service.</span>\r\n<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Origins Of The Moving Industry</span></h2>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">A number of years before the advent of the wheel, migrating people engineered different methods to move large items long distances starting with wooden sled-like structures that were dragged behind steeds or by hand. The French called these trailers travois. At that point as people entered different periods throughout history, they started to move less frequently. Groups of people began settling in regions and migration began to slow. About the same time, innovation in the moving process began making strides. The wheel was created and it incredibly expanded productivity. Wheels, in conjunction with axles, got to be one of the six basic machines. The wheel directly gave rise to the wooden truck, the wagon, and the steam powered train. These other more advanced techniques for transportation gave individuals the capacity to move their possessions over large swaths of land, quickly and efficiently. America\'s expansion into the West gave ever increasing need to move bigger and bigger loads across longer stretches of land.</span>\r\n<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Advent of the Modern Day Moving Company</span></h2>\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-178" src="http://192.168.0.2/wp-content/uploads/advent-of-moving-company.jpg" alt="Movers Mechanization " width="960" height="640" />\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Individuals didn\'t begin paying others to move them until the mid nineteenth century. The rush to expand West in America began to happen and the importance of moving became a greater need. Individuals began moving small distances by packing up customers belongings into horse drawn wagons first and greatly began to expand with the advent of the gas powered engine. Moving started out as a primarily family-based business with generations of families entering the business year after year.  The well off families would pay men to move their belongings into wagons and after that ship them to distribution centers, most of the time located somewhere on the railway. The moving company would then load them into a train carty and transport them to another distribution center for loading and unloading. From that last distribution center the shipment would be packed onto a wagon and then unpacked at the family\'s new house. These early moving organizations were the beginning of the moving business. At the end of WWII, a great many soldiers fighting returned home. With the war at a close and an attention on residential life, the era of post war America started and with it came an enormous expansion in America\'s population and the need for moving services began to rise.</span>\r\n<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Keep On Trucking</span></h2>\r\n<img class="wp-image-180" src="http://192.168.0.2/wp-content/uploads/moving-truck.jpg" alt="Movers Truck" width="650" height="433" />\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The moving business has kept on trucking and it’s estimated that over 40 million Americans move yearly. The moving business itself earns 16 billion dollars a year. The industry is mainly divided into little and medium-sized moving companies. Customers hire movers to take on jobs of all sizes. There\'s an unmistakable difference between moving companies that spend significant time in long distance moves and those that have practical experience in little neighborhood moves. For the future, I\'d anticipate the market will develop for any measured mover. While hiring a mover today, you want to make sure they are licensed and bonded.</span>', 'History Of The Moving Company', 'The moving industry has existed in some form or fashion throughout most of civilization. Starting with hunter gathers, people needed to move large objects across log stretches of land. This article explores the history of the modern day moving company and traces the history of the moving industry in general.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '167-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-11 06:14:24', '2016-11-11 06:14:24', '', 167, 'http://192.168.0.2/167-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(196, 1, '2016-11-11 06:17:47', '2016-11-11 06:17:47', 'Congrats, you got that big promotion! You race home to tell the family about the amazing news and midway through you forget you also have to tell them the jobs in New York. Aside from having to find a <a href="http://siraustinmovers.com/long-distance-moving/">long distance moving company</a> you remember you\'ll have to break the news to your kids. Rather than being super excited about your promotion your kids are filled with fear. They’ve never been anywhere but the home they know and if they’re like most kids they have a fear of the unknown.\r\n<h2>Setting Up The Pins For The Big Move</h2>\r\n<img class="wp-image-185" src="http://192.168.0.2/wp-content/uploads/moving-bowling-pins.jpg" alt="Moving Pins" width="500" height="500" />\r\n\r\nLuckily there are things that you can do to mitigate against their fears and while a new move can be stressful for anyone, especially kids, you can make them feel safe at home in a number of different ways. Concentrate on the positive aspects of the move and try and shy away from any negative things associated with it. Urge your children to discuss their true feelings and not hide anything that may be bothering them\r\n\r\nHelp your children say farewell to their home and their friends by having a big going away party so they can officially say goodbye to their friends. Make sure to throw a real bash, of course one that your budget will allow. Invite everyone that they would really want to see before they leave, that way they can take those memories with them right through the move.\r\n<h2>Don’t Pack Up ALL The Toys</h2>\r\nWhile space may be tight during the move you should have enough space for a few favorite toys. Having toys on a long move will help keep them occupied so they’ll feel at home. A good way to do this is to have a dedicated box where you can store the toys as you move. Chasing through boxes at the end of your move will only cause headache so it would definitely best to avoid that outcome.\r\n<h2>Make Sure To Have Friends (aka sitters) Around</h2>\r\nIf you don’t have a dedicated nanny (lucky you if you do!) a great way to alleviate stress, theirs AND yours, would be to have a few of your friends around. Now we advise when telling your friend to help out posing it like that’s all they’ll be doing, then you ask them to do a bunch of stuff once they get there. Masking it this way is a great way to sucker a few extra friends to help out with your move ;)\r\n<h2>Are We There Yet?</h2>\r\n<img class="wp-image-192" src="http://192.168.0.2/wp-content/uploads/are-we-there-yet.png" alt="Are We There Yet" width="400" height="400" />\r\n\r\nIf possible, try and stay away from the electronics during the move and have fun. A move of great magnitude will be a major milestone in your children\'s life so make sure to smell the roses on the ride. You want the trip to be memorable because if the move is permanent then your kids will remember the experience for many years to come. So research cool games that you can play along the way as a family. There are a number of different websites that you can find cool games on. If you can’t find a good website then Google will be your friend here.\r\n<h2>Moving In To Your New Home</h2>\r\nOnce arriving at your new home then don’t unpack right away. If you have a few days off before you have to start work then plan a few days of sightseeing in your new city. Great things to do are going to a movie, eating at a great restaurant, or visiting any theme parks that might be nearby. Not unpacking right away will alleviate not just stress for your children but also for you. Besides, you worked so hard that big promotion, kick your feet back as well!Congratulations, you got that big promotion! Only downside is that you have to relocate thousands of miles away. Preparing your kids for a long distance move can be a daunting task, bit it doesn\'t have to be! Follow the advice in this aricle for a seamless long distance move', 'Preparing For A Long Distance Move', 'Congratulations, you got that big promotion! Only downside is that you have to relocate thousands of miles away. Preparing your kids for a long distance move can be a daunting task, bit it doesn\'t have to be! Follow the advice in this aricle for a seamless long distance move', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '183-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-11 06:17:47', '2016-11-11 06:17:47', '', 183, 'http://192.168.0.2/183-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
