(311, 1, '2016-11-13 20:14:11', '2016-11-13 20:14:11', '[vc_row row_type="row" use_row_as_full_screen_section="no" type="full_width" angled_section="no" text_align="left" background_image_as_pattern="without_pattern" background_color="#ffffff" css_animation=""][vc_column][vc_gmaps link="#E-8_"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row row_type="row" use_row_as_full_screen_section="no" type="grid" angled_section="no" text_align="left" background_image_as_pattern="without_pattern" background_color="#ffffff" padding_top="50" padding_bottom="34" css_animation=""][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">South Austin Is SOOO SoCo</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_separator type="small" position="left" up="7" down="13"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4>Sir Thinks South Austin Has The Best Food Trucks Anywhere!</h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_separator type="transparent" up="24" down="0"][vc_column_text]South Austin moves are a lot like East Austin moves in that the two main concerns you have are low lying trees and potholes. Because South Austin was one of the first developed parts of the city outside downtown, many of the streets are older and have more trees. Therefore keeping a watchful eye on both are crucial components to having a great move.[/vc_column_text][vc_separator type="transparent" up="15" down="0"][vc_column_text]Another South Austin moving condition that is important is door size. Because many of the houses are a little older the door sizes and usually smaller and the moving impediments are generally greater. That\'s why measuring everything becomes more critical during the planning phase. For instance if you\'re moving a refrigerator how big is it? If it\'s a double door fridge how did it get there? Did the original movers have to take off any doors? What was the original path of entry? Answering these questions ahead of time will prepare our movers for whatever is going to come there way.[/vc_column_text][vc_separator type="transparent" up="42" down="0"]